Residents of Mai Mahiu town in Naivasha yesterday found the decapitated body of a man dumped by the roadside.  The body, found near Kariandusi open field, lay in a pool of blood, with the head a few meters away.  The residents recovered documents, a mobile phone, and some cash from the deceased. The police suspect that the man was killed in a revenge attack. Joseph Njoroge, a witness, said they notified the authorities immediately they found the body.        Extension of Sh3.5b meter-gauge railway line complete  Extension of Sh3.5b meter-gauge railway line complete  Police officer killed, seven people injured in accidents  Naivasha hopes to save more lives with improved hospital  Cargo pile up reduces at Nairobi Inland Container Depot  KeNHA announces Narok-Mai Mahiu Road temporarily closed as motorists urged to use alternative routes  Kituo cha treni ya SGR Mai Mahiu chasalia kufungwa juma moja baada ya kuzinduliwa By Edward Kosut | 8 hours ago By Nikko Tanui | 8 hours ago By James Munyeki | 8 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 14 hours ago